  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6999.1 sitting right at the massive 7000 gamma wall (19.2B), dealers are aggressively selling into this rally attempt as they're long gamma in PIN regime. The -4.5% 1-minute drop suggests dealers just successfully defended the 7000 level, and with the flip strike well below at 6875, any further weakness should trigger dealer buying support. Key level to watch is whether we can reclaim 7000 decisively or if dealers continue capping rallies here, with the 6800 negative gamma zone as downside magnet if selling accelerates.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect strong resistance at 7000 with potential chop between here and 6875.",
